'''''Global Spin: The Corporate Assault on Environmentalism''''' is a book by Professor [[Sharon Beder]]. It was first published in 1997 and there have been subsequent updated editions in 2000 and 2002. The book uses many detailed case studies to build up a "bigger picture" of how [[multinational corporations|large corporations]] attempt to manipulate [[environmental issues]] for their own ends. In the first edition most of the material was from the United States, where the corporate environmental impact has been greatest.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Edwards, David|date=November 1997|title=Global Spin review|url=|journal=The Ecologist|volume= 27| issue = 6|pages=251â2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Myers|first=Allen|date=1997|title=Diagnosing the methods of spin doctors|url=|journal=Green Left Weekly|volume=229|page=26}}</ref>
==See also== *[[List of Australian environmental books]] *[[Unequal Protection: The Rise of Corporate Dominance and the Theft of Human Rights]]
