'''OLB5''' was the callsign of a Czech [[time signal]] radio station. The station was located at [[PodÄbrady]] and transmitted time signals which originated from the [[OMA (time signal)]] clock at [[RKS Liblice 1|Liblice]]. 

The station transmitted in the [[high frequency|HF]] band, on 3.17&nbsp;MHz with 1&nbsp;kW.<ref>{{cite book | author=Gerd Klawitter | title=List of Time Signal Stations (9th Edition) | year=1980 | pages=21â22 }}</ref>

